{
  "stem": "2353.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And 1947, my first son was born. 1951, my second son was born.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was praying for that son in the worst way.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't want a girl, because my mother and I had a terrible relationship all our lives.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I figured if that's the kind of relationship you have with a mother, I'd rather have a son, another son, than a daughter.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And to the great regret of my husband, who loves girls of all ages, we had this second son.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was very happy about it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I'm still very happy about it, because they're two great kids.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You mean my mother and father?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my mother and father, they-- they were able to-- to go to England, as I said before.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when the war broke out, they-- the English took them, all the-- like they took the Japanese here, and took all the Jewish refugees, and I suppose the Germans, too, if they had any there, and put them into-- into a camp.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they separated my mother and my father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my-- my brother stayed with my mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they already had the visa to come over here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And still they interred them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the thing that made me hate the English so much, when-- they were supposed to wait for their passage to go-- to come here, and it was very hard, because there was-- there were already U-boats around.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it-- it-- the traffic between England and Europe and-- and the United States was very limited.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So finally, there was a boat ready for them in Liverpool.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when they took them to Liverpool under guard, my mother and father, you know, criminals.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when they arrived in Liverpool, the-- the ship wasn't ready yet.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
